                <p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Terms and Conditions:</strong> these CarSloter Europe terms and conditions;</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Transport Documents:</strong> all duly and fully completed transport document as required in relation to, and as are necessary to prove the transport of the Vehicle from one place to another, including without limitation CMR consignment note, export documents or certificates of delivery;</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Transport Fees:</strong> the amount payable by Buyer for transport of the Vehicles;</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Triangulation Scheme:</strong> a chain transaction between three parties located in three different EU Member States (A-B-C) where the goods/Vehicles are shipped directly from the first Member State (A) to the last (C). At CarSloter Europe all transport is organised on behalf of CarSloter Europe NV or CarSloter Europe NV affiliates unless explicitely specified;</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>User:</strong> has the meaning given to it in clause 4.1.1;</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Vehicle:</strong> any vehicle advertised via the Platform;</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Vehicle Documents:</strong> any and all official documents relating to the Vehicle (including without limitation certificate of conformity and inspection documents);</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Vehicle Information:</strong> any photos, description, information, documentation and/or other materials regarding the Vehicle advertised via the Platform during the Auction, including the CarSloter Europe Vehicle Description.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;"> <a name="3">&nbsp;</a> </p>
                <h3 style="text-align: justify;">3. Platform registration</h3>
                <br>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">3.1 The Platform is exclusively available for and may only be used by professional and recognised car dealers duly registered.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">3.2 To be authorized to access and use the Platform, Buyer must request confirmation of registration by duly completing the Registration Form and sending all required documents in accordance with the registration modalities described on the Platform, and by accepting these Terms and Conditions.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">3.3 The person completing and submitting the Registration Form, and accepting these Terms and Conditions on behalf of Buyer represents and warrants having the necessary powers to legally commit the Buyer.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">3.4 Depending on the registered office of the Buyer, and subject to the applicable VAT regulations, Buyer may be offered the possibility to choose from which member of the CarSloter Europe it wishes to receive invoices under these Terms and Conditions. If Buyer is</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">3.4.1 offered this possibility, for the purposes of these Terms and Conditions, CarSloter Europe shall be the member of the CarSloter Europe chosen by Buyer and such entity shall be Buyer's sole contracting party for any dealings between the Parties governed by these Terms and Conditions and shall be the entity invoicing Buyer. If Buyer wishes to subsequently modify its choice, such modification shall be subject to CarSloter Europe's prior approval; and</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">3.4.2 not offered this possibility, for the purposes of these Terms and Conditions CarSloter Europe shall be CarSloter Europe NV, and CarSloter Europe NV shall be Buyer's sole contracting party for any dealings between the Parties governed by these Terms and Conditions and shall be the entity invoicing Buyer.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">3.4.3 CarSloter Europe might decide, without justification or advance notice, to invoice from CarSloter Europe NV location or from the country where the Buyer is registered. Such change shall not open the right to any type of claim or cancellation; </p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">3.5 Buyer guarantees that all information and/or documents provided are correct, complete and valid. Buyer shall promptly notify CarSloter Europe of any changes in the information mentioned in the Registration Form and/or documents submitted under clause 3.2. Notwithstanding clause 3.6, Buyer acknowledges and accepts that CarSloter Europe bears no liability regarding verification of the information and documentation provided by Buyer.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">3.6 CarSloter Europe has at any time (before or after confirmation of Buyer's registration) the right to verify the accuracy of the information contained in the Registration Form and/or the validity of the documents submitted by Buyer under clause 3.2. If such verification reveals any inaccuracy of information and/or any invalidity of documentation, without prejudice to its other rights and remedies under these Terms and Conditions or otherwise, CarSloter Europe reserves the right to</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">3.6.1 reject Buyer's request for registration. CarSloter Europe will inform Buyer of such rejection and may, in its sole discretion, determine to provide Buyer with the opportunity to rectify any such inaccuracies and/or invalidities; or</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">3.6.2 suspend or permanently block Buyer's and its Users' access to and use of the Platform in accordance with clause 4.6. </p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">3.7 CarSloter Europe reserves at all times the right to refuse confirmation of a registration request without motivation. CarSloter Europe shall not be liable for any Losses suffered or incurred by Buyer arising out of or in connection with any such refusal.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">3.8 If CarSloter Europe decides to approve Buyer's request for registration, CarSloter Europe will inform Buyer thereof and provide Buyer with one or more Means of Access for the Platform. Buyer shall not be able to submit any Offers until such approval by CarSloter Europe and receipt of the Means of Access.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;"> <a name="4">&nbsp;</a> </p>
                <h3 style="text-align: justify;">4. Platform Access and Use</h3>
                <br>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">4.1 Users and use in general</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">4.1.1 Buyer acknowledges and accepts that he is responsible for the actions and omissions performed by all users making use of the Platform on behalf of Buyer or otherwise via Buyer's Means of Access ("Users"). Buyer shall provide all Users with a copy of these Terms and Conditions, shall comply with these, and make sure each User complies with these Terms and Conditions. </p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">4.1.2 Buyer warrants that the Platform is used in accordance with these Terms and Conditions, all applicable national and international legislation and, in general, in a responsible manner, exclusively for its own and admissible professional purposes and without breach of the rights of third parties. Neither Buyer nor the Users are permitted to make modifications to the Platform. Buyer is liable for and will hold harmless and indemnify CarSloter Europe against any Losses suffered or incurred by CarSloter Europe arising out of or in connection with any (i) modifications made to Platform; and/or (ii) use of the Platform in a manner that does not correspond with these Terms and Conditions.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">4.1.3 Buyer undertakes not to use, and will ensure none of its Users uses the Platform to (i) download, send, or disseminate data containing viruses, worms, spyware, malware or any other similar malicious programs; (ii) carry out any calculations, operations or transactions that may interrupt, destroy or restrict the functionality of the operation of the Platform or any program, computer or means of telecommunications; (iii) submit any information or materials which infringe third party rights, are libellous, obscene, threatening or otherwise unlawful; and/or (iv) submit any non-binding Offers.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">4.2 Required hardware, software and services</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">Buyer acknowledges and agrees that it is responsible for the choice, purchase and operation of the hardware, software and/or telecommunication services required to connect with and to use the Platform. Such hardware, software and/or telecommunication services need to meet the minimum requirements as may be specified from time to time on the Platform. Buyer is responsible for the installation and related costs of purchasing and/or licensing such hardware, software and/or telecommunication services. CarSloter Europe is not liable for hardware, software, products and services of third parties, such as telecommunication equipment, internet connections, operating systems and internet browsers.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">4.3 Security and Means of Access</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">4.3.1 Use of the Platform requires Means of Access. Means of Access are strictly personal and Buyer is responsible for the safeguarding, confidentiality, security and appropriate use of the Means of Access by him and its Users and undertakes to take all steps to prevent any unauthorized third party from gaining knowledge and making use thereof. Buyer shall not transfer or sell any Means of Access to any third party, except Users who are duly authorised to act on its behalf.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">4.3.2 Buyer will notify CarSloter Europe immediately by email or fax of the loss, theft, breach of confidentiality or any risk of misuse of the Means of Access. Buyer is fully and unconditionally responsible for any use of the Platform and any Offers made, as well as for any detrimental consequences that may arise directly or indirectly therefrom, until one (1) Business Day after such notification has been made.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">4.3.3 If CarSloter Europe has any reason to suspect that the confidentiality and/or security of the Means of Access has been breached or that the Platform is being misused, CarSloter Europe may, without prior notice, suspend access to the Platform, at its sole discretion and without opening the right for any type of compensation.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">4.3.4 Buyer acknowledges having been warned that CarSloter Europe reserves the right to refuse access to a User using Means of Access when a session is already open on another computer where another User is using the same Means of Access.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">4.3.5 CarSloter Europe has the righ to suspend for a definite or indefinite period any account for any reason. This includes, without limitation, the delay in car payment, suspiscious behavior, suspiscion of fraud or VAT carousel or any other type of reason that CarSloter Europe does not need to communicate to the Buyer. </p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">4.3.6 CarSloter Europe shall not be liable for any Losses suffered or incurred by Buyer arising out of or in connection with any such suspended or refused access as described in clauses 4.3.3 4.3.4 and 4.3.5.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">4.4 Platform services fees</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">CarSloter Europe may, from time to time, offer certain services via the Platform which are subject to payment of the applicable fees by Buyer, and/or require payment of a fee by Buyer for existing services. The applicable fees shall be indicated via the Platform and may vary from time to time. Buyer shall be solely responsible to verify the applicable fees each time Buyer (or its Users) access and use the Platform and/or services offered via the Platform.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">4.5 Intellectual property rights</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">4.5.1 The intellectual and industrial property rights and know-how associated with the Platform belong exclusively to CarSloter Europe. CarSloter Europe grants Buyer and its Users a non-transferable, limited, non-exclusive license to use the Platform for Buyer's own business purposes only, until CarSloter Europe blocks Buyer's and/or its Users' access to the Platform.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">4.5.2 Buyer shall take all necessary measures to protect and ensure that its Users protect CarSloter Europe's intellectual and industrial property rights.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">4.5.3 Without prejudice to the rights of Buyer and Users under the legislation relating to the protection of computer programs of which cannot be contractually deviated, Buyer and its Users may not: (i) modify, translate or adapt the Platform in any way; (ii) decompile or disassemble the Platform in any way; (iii) copy the Platform in any way; (iv) pass on, dispose of, grant as a sub-license, lease, lend or distribute the Platform or documentation in any way to third parties; (v) create any product or service substantially similar to the Platform; and/or (vi) copy any ideas, characteristics and/or functions of the Platform. CarSloter Europe reserves the sole right to correct any errors.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">4.6 Suspension and blocking</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">4.6.1 Buyer acknowledges and agrees that CarSloter Europe reserves the right to suspend Buyer's and its Users' access to the Platform for any reason, including without limitation (i) in case of actual or reasonably suspected breach by Buyer and/or its Users of these Terms and Conditions; (ii) in case of an attack on CarSloter Europe's IT systems; (iii) if legally required; (iv) so as to avoid or mitigate any detrimental impact on CarSloter Europe, Buyer and/or the Buyer Community; and (v) for purposes of Platform maintenance. CarSloter Europe will use reasonable efforts to inform Buyer of such suspension as soon as practically possible.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">4.6.2 Buyer acknowledges and agrees that CarSloter Europe reserves the right to permanently block Buyer's and its Users' access to the Platform (i) in case of breach by Buyer and/or its Users of these Terms and Conditions; (ii) in the circumstances described in clause 12; and (iii) in case of fraudulent practices of Buyer and/or its Users; (iv) for any other reason at the descretion of CarSloter Europe.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;"> <a name="5">&nbsp;</a> </p>
                <h3 style="text-align: justify;">5. Auctions and Offers</h3>
                <br>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">5.1 Auctions</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">5.1.1 The Platform provides Sellers with the possibility to advertise Vehicles which they intend to sell. Such Vehicles may, at CarSloter Europe's sole discretion, be advertised separately or combined into one or more sets of Vehicles.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">5.1.2 Each member of the Buyer Community has the possibility to submit a binding offer for the purchase of such set of Vehicles from CarSloter Europe, by submitting an Offer (Purchase price out of Taxes and costs) at which such member of the Buyer Community offers to purchase such Vehicles from CarSloter Europe ("Buyer Community Offers").</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">5.1.3 Buyer Community Offers will be assessed by CarSloter Europe until after Auction Closing and CarSloter Europe will determine, in its sole discretion, if it is willing to sell such set of Vehicles to the member of the Buyer Community which submitted the best offer. Buyer expressly acknowledges and agrees that its Offer may be excluded from this assessment if CarSloter Europe reasonably considers that its Offer is incorrect (for example and without limitation in case of an abnormally high price). CarSloter Europe shall not be liable for any Losses suffered or incurred by Buyer arising out of or in connection with any such exclusion.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">5.1.4 Buyer expressly acknowledges and agrees that any sale of any Vehicle by CarSloter Europe to any member of the Buyer Community is dependent on Seller agreeing to sell the Vehicle to CarSloter Europe, and that submission of the best Buyer Community Offer does not guarantee that Buyer will be able to purchase the Vehicle.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">5.1.5 Neither CarSloter Europe nor the Seller shall be liable for any Losses suffered or incurred by Buyer arising out of or in connection with any decision from Seller or CarSloter Europe to cancel or otherwise not proceed with an Auction at any time.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">5.1.6 Buyer shall be informed of the applicable Auction Fees and Country Fees for each Vehicle that is part of the Auction, via the Platform. Buyer expressly acknowledges and agrees that the Auction Fees and Country Fees may vary per Vehicle and per Auction.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">5.2 Offers</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">5.2.1 In case Buyer wishes to purchases a (set of) Vehicle(s), Buyer has the option to submit an Offer for the purchase of such Vehicle(s). An Offer shall always consist of the Purchase price excluding taxes and costs Buyer is offering to pay for such Vehicles to CarSloter Europe ("Offered Price").</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">5.2.2   Buyer expressly acknowledges and agrees that any Offer submitted via the Platform shall constitute a binding offer, which cannot be withdrawn by Buyer until expiry of a period of forty-eight (48) hours (calculated over Business Days only) as from Auction Closing.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">5.2.3   In case Buyer submits more than one (1) Offer for the same Vehicle, only the highest Offer of Buyer will be taken into account by CarSloter Europe.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">5.2.4   Buyer acknowledges and agrees that submission and acceptance of Offers shall always be subject to the applicable Auction Rules.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">5.2.5   Buyer and its Users shall not manipulate the price of any Vehicle advertised during an Auction and shall not in any way interfere with offers made by other members of the Buyer Community.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;"> <a name="6">&nbsp;</a> </p>
                <h3 style="text-align: justify;">6. CarSloter Europe Sales</h3>
                <br>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">6.1 CarSloter Europe Sale Confirmation</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">6.1.1 If (i) Buyer's Offer is deemed to be the best Buyer Community Offer in accordance with clause 6.1.3, (ii) CarSloter Europe is able to purchase the Vehicle(s) concerned from Seller and (iii) CarSloter Europe decides to accept such Offer in accordance with clause 5.1.3, CarSloter Europe sells the Vehicle(s) concerned to Buyer ("CarSloter Europe Sale"). The Vehicle(s) shall be sold at the Offered Price, to be increased with the Auction Fees, Country Fees, Transport Fees and all applicable Taxes .</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">6.1.2 In such case, CarSloter Europe will inform Buyer of the CarSloter Europe Sale, and Buyer is required to confirm via the Platform the administrative delivery details of the CarSloter Europe Sale within twenty-four (24) hours (one business day) as from receipt of such information from CarSloter Europe ("CarSloter Europe Sale Confirmation"). Buyer expressly acknowledges and agrees that the CarSloter Europe Sale Confirmation is an administrative formality to organise delivery and shall not be construed as a possibility for Buyer to cancel its Offer and/or otherwise cancel the CarSloter Europe Sale.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">6.1.3 In the CarSloter Europe Sale Confirmation, Buyer shall confirm in any case the country of destination of the purchased Vehicle(s). Buyer shall be solely responsible for any costs, expenses, Taxes and any other consequences related to its choice of country of destination. CarSloter Europe shall not be liable for any Losses suffered or incurred by Buyer arising out of or in connection with the chosen country of destination.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">6.2 Payment and invoicing of CarSloter Europe Sales</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">6.2.1 For each CarSloter Europe Sale, the Offered Price will be increased with all Taxes which shall be payable by Buyer. The Taxes will include the VAT due, if any, in the country of residence of the member of the CarSloter Europe invoicing the CarSloter Europe Sale. In case of an Intra-Community Supply or Export, and as far as there is sufficient Evidence of the transport of the Vehicle, no VAT will be due on the CarSloter Europe Sale and Buyer will be liable to account for the VAT due in the country of destination.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">Unless the Vehicle is at the time of the sale located in Belgium, the Intra-Community Supplies are treated for VAT purposes as a “Triangulation Scheme” (cf. so-called ABC transactions). This implies that the Buyer shall take care, in the EU Member State of arrival, of the required VAT formalities as the last link in the chain (cf. party C).</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">6.2.2 At the time CarSloter Europe informs Buyer of the CarSloter Europe Sale under clause 6.1.2, CarSloter Europe will provide Buyer with an order form, which sets out (i) the Purchase Price, consisting of the Offered Price, the Auction Fees, the Country Fees, the Transport Fees and any applicable Taxes; and (ii) any guarantee payable by Buyer pursuant to clause 7.4.2. Buyer shall ensure that the Purchase Price is credited to the bank account of CarSloter Europe as specified on the order form at the latest forty-eight (48) hours (calculated over Business Days only) after submission of the CarSloter Europe Sale Confirmation. </p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">6.2.3 CarSloter Europe will issue the invoice for each CarSloter Europe Sale after receipt of the Purchase Price on CarSloter Europe bank account.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;"> <a name="7">&nbsp;</a> </p>
                <h3 style="text-align: justify;">7. Transport and delivery of vehicles and Vehicle Documents</h3>
                <br>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">7.1 General</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">7.1.1 Transport of the Vehicle will be performed by or on behalf of CarSloter Europe. At Buyer's option, Buyer is entitled to take care of the transport of the Vehicle on behalf of CarSloter Europe.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">7.1.2 Any Vehicle shall, and may only be, transported to the country of destination as indicated on the CarSloter Europe Sale Confirmation. Buyer is liable for and will hold harmless and indemnify CarSloter Europe against any Losses suffered or incurred by CarSloter Europe arising out of or in connection with transport of a Vehicle to any country other than the country of destination as indicated on the CarSloter Europe Sale Confirmation.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">7.1.3 Property of the Vehicle shall transfer at the sending of the car documents to the Buyer. The Properlty is not transferred at pickup, but only after approval of the FCMR (delivery evidence) by CarSloter Europe. Risk related to the vehicle shall transfer at the earliest of (i) pick-up of the Vehicle by Buyer; (ii) delivery of the vehicle at the destination indicated by the Buyer and (iii) expiry of a two (2) weeks period (or such shorter period as set out on the pick-up authorisation document) as from receipt of the pick-up authorisation document.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">7.2 Transport of Vehicles arranged by CarSloter Europe</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">This clause 7.2 shall apply in case CarSloter Europe arranges for transport of Vehicles, in addition to the CarSloter Europe terms and conditions relating to transport available via the Platform.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">7.2.1 Prices for transport mentioned on the Platform are indicative and non-binding, and the actual Transport Fees for transport will depend on several criteria, including without limitation physical location of the Vehicle and type of Vehicle. Any prices mentioned on the Platform are exclusive of applicable Taxes.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">7.2.2 Transport shall not be organised by CarSloter Europe until the later of (i) the moment the Purchase Price is credited to CarSloter Europe's bank account mentioned on the order form; and (ii) release of the Vehicle by the Seller.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">7.2.3 Any times or dates for delivery by or on behalf of CarSloter Europe are estimates and shall not be of the essence. Save in case of its own fraud or willful intent, CarSloter Europe shall not be liable for any delay in delivery. Delay in delivery of any Vehicles shall not relieve Buyer of its obligation to accept delivery.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">7.3 Transport of Vehicles arranged by Buyer on behalf of CarSloter Europe</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">This clause 7.3 shall apply in case Buyer organises transport of Vehicles on behalf of CarSloter Europe.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">7.3.1 The Vehicle shall not be available for pick-up and transportation until the later of (i) the moment the Purchase Price is credited to CarSloter Europe's bank account mentioned on the order form; (ii) release of the Vehicle by the Seller; and (iii) issuance of the pick-up authorisation document(s) to Buyer.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">7.3.2 Buyer shall pick up and transport the Vehicle at the latest within two (2) weeks (or such shorter time frame as set out on the pick-up authorisation document) of receipt of the pick-up authorisation document. Buyer acknowledges and agrees that CarSloter Europe, Seller or the third party storing the Vehicle on their behalf, has at all times the right to refuse delivery of a Vehicle to Buyer (or Buyer's transporter, as applicable) in case Buyer (or Buyer's transporter, as applicable) does not present a valid pick-up authorisation document. Buyer shall be fully responsible for any Losses incurred by Buyer, CarSloter Europe, Seller or the third party arising out of or in connection with such lack of valid pick-up authorisation document.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">7.3.3 In case Buyer fails to pick up the Vehicle within</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">(a) two (2) weeks (or such shorter time frame as set out on the pick-up authorisation document) of receipt of the pick-up authorisation document, CarSloter Europe reserves the right to charge Buyer an amount of forty euros (EUR 40.00) administration costs and up to five euros (EUR 5.00) per day until pick-up of the Vehicle;</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">(b) one (1) month of the CarSloter Europe Sale Confirmation, the CarSloter Europe Sale shall be deemed wrongfully cancelled by Buyer in accordance with clause 12.4.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">7.4 Proof of transport and Vehicle Documents</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">7.4.1 Intra-Community Supply</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">(a) In case of Intra-Community Supply, Buyer shall submit to CarSloter Europe all required Evidence and Transport Documents regarding the Vehicle and the country of destination duly completed.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">(b) Buyer acknowledges and agrees that:</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">(i) regardless of whether transport was arranged for by or on behalf of CarSloter Europe, in case CarSloter Europe reasonably doubts the validity or completeness of the Transport Documents submitted by Buyer, CarSloter Europe reserves the right to retain the Vehicle Documents until such time as Buyer submits valid Evidence; and</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">(ii) CarSloter Europe shall not deliver the Vehicle Documents until receipt of the correctly filled out Transport Documents and Evidence.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">7.4.2 Export</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">(a) In case of Export, Buyer shall submit to CarSloter Europe all required Evidence and Export Documents regarding the Vehicle and the country of destination duly completed.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">(b) In case of Export, pending transfer and receipt of the necessary Export Document, CarSloter Europe requires, per Vehicle that is exported to a non-EU country, a guarantee equal to the sum of the VAT amount that would be due in the country of residence of the member of the CarSloter Europe invoicing the CarSloter Europe Sale, in the event the CarSloter Europe Sale should not constitute an export for VAT purposes. The guarantee amount will be mentioned separately on the order form.&nbsp;The guarantee is twenty one per cent (21%) of the vehicle price with a minimum of five hundred euros (EUR 500,00).</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">(c) Upon receipt of the necessary Evidence and Export Documents by CarSloter Europe from Buyer, proving that the CarSloter Europe Sale constitutes an export for VAT purposes, the amount of the guarantee will be reimbursed on the Buyers bank account and the CarSloter Europe Sale will be invoiced to Buyer without VAT.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">7.4.3 Save in case of its own fraud or wilful intent, CarSloter Europe shall not be liable for any Losses suffered or incurred by Buyer (including without limitation unability to register the Vehicle) arising out of or in connection with any missing or incomplete Vehicle Documents.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">7.5 Sending of car documents&nbsp; <br>
                <br>
                CarSloter Europe will send the car documents to the VAT registration country of the Buyer after reception and validation of the delivery Evidence and after receipt in full of the Increased Purchase Price. The Buyer keeps the full responsibility for the appropriate declaration of the purchase to the authorities. CarSloter Europe responsibility will in no case be engaged for any error, mistake or forgetfulness committed by the Buyer in relation with applicable taxes (VAT or any other tax). </p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;"> <a name="8">&nbsp;</a> </p>
                <h3 style="text-align: justify;">8. Vehicle Information</h3>
                <br>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">8.1 Buyer acknowledges and agrees that it acts as a professional car dealer with thorough knowledge of the sector of used cars and the issues typically associated with used cars and the used cars business.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">8.2 Buyer acknowledges and accepts that CarSloter Europe's commercially advantageous offerings regarding the Platform and the related services render it impossible for CarSloter Europe to carry out a detailed technical inspection of every Vehicle advertised by a Seller on the Platform, and to assume responsibility in that respect. Buyer acknowledges and accepts that all Vehicle Information is based on the information obtained from the Seller.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">To the maximum extent permitted by law, without prejudice to clause 9, and save in case of its own fraud or wilful intent, CarSloter Europe shall not be responsible for, and not be liable for any Losses suffered or incurred by Buyer arising out of or in connection with any inaccuracy in or incompleteness of the Vehicle Information (including without limitation in relation to mileage, damage, technical faults, optional extras, colour, year of manufacture, date of first registration, etc.).</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">To the maximum extent permitted by law, CarSloter Europe expressly excludes any liability for Losses arising out of or in connection with third party fraud (including without limitation mileage, margin status and/or chassis number fraud).</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">8.3 Vehicle Information may, depending on the Vehicle, consist of one or more types of information, each of which shall be clearly identified as such on the Platform, including the following:</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">8.3.1 the CarSloter Europe Vehicle Description; and</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">8.3.2 reports from external third parties and photos.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">8.4 Buyer expressly acknowledges that</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">8.4.1 each of these types of information are made or created at different points in time, and may as such not always correctly reflect the status of the Vehicle at the moment of the sale of the Vehicle occurs;</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">8.4.2 Buyer has no access over any Vehicle Information other than the CarSloter Europe Vehicle Description and as a result, any such other Vehicle Information is provided for Buyer's convenience only;</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">8.4.3 to determine if the Vehicle as delivered to Buyer is in conformity, only the CarSloter Europe Vehicle Description shall be taken into account; and</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">8.4.4 in case of any conflict or ambiguity between the CarSloter Europe Vehicle Description and any other Vehicle Information, the CarSloter Europe Vehicle Description shall always prevail. </p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;"> <a name="9">&nbsp;</a> </p>
                <h3 style="text-align: justify;">9. Limited warranty</h3>
                <br>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">9.1 For Vehicles which are not designated as "wrecked cars", “technical damaged cars”, “body damaged cars” and “accident cars” during the Auction, and always subject to clause 10.5,</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">9.1.1 CarSloter Europe solely warrants that on the date of delivery the Vehicle conforms to the CarSloter Europe Vehicle Description. If and to the extent a Vehicle fails to meet such warranty, as shall be determined in accordance with clause 10, CarSloter Europe has the right to issue a credit note for any such Vehicle in the amount of the reasonably estimated decrease in value of the Vehicle resulting from the damage to the Vehicle which was not indicated in the CarSloter Europe Vehicle Description. In the event CarSloter Europe makes such credit, such credit amount shall be Buyer's sole remedy; and</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">9.1.2 the validity of any warranty claim by Buyer shall be contingent upon receipt by CarSloter Europe of timely notice of any alleged non-conformance of the Vehicle in accordance with clause 10.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">9.2 For Vehicles which are designated as "wrecked cars", “technical damaged cars”, “body damaged cars” and “accident cars” during the Auction, Buyer expressly acknowledges and agrees that, to the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, CarSloter Europe provides no warranty of any kind, including without limitation any warranty of conformity or merchantability.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">9.3 The warranty set out in this clause 9 is exclusive and in lieu of all other warranties, representations, conditions or other terms, express, implied, statutory, contractually or otherwise, including, without limitation, any warranty of merchantability or suitability or fitness for any purpose.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">9.4 The warranty set out in this clause 9 shall not apply if and to the extent the non-conformity results from (i) modifications made to and any other works performed on the Vehicle by or on behalf of Buyer; and/or (ii) use of the Vehicle by or on behalf of Buyer other than with reasonable care and skill.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;"> <a name="10">&nbsp;</a> </p>
                <h3 style="text-align: justify;">10.    Conformity and complaints</h3>
                <br>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">10.1 On delivery of the Vehicle, Buyer shall examine (or have examined on its behalf) the Vehicle and satisfy itself that the Vehicle complies with the CarSloter Europe Vehicle Description. During such examination, Buyer shall at all times take into account (i) the fact that Buyer purchased a used vehicle; (ii) the Vehicle's mileage; and (iii) the Vehicle's first registration date. Defects in or damage to parts of the Vehicle do not entitle Buyer to reject the entire Vehicle.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">10.2 Complaints about the Vehicle shall be made using the CarSloter Europe complaints form and:</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">10.2.1 in respect of any defect or damage which would be apparent from a reasonable inspection on delivery, shall be mentioned on CMR and/or consignment note; </p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">10.2.2 in respect of any hidden defect or damage, shall be made at the latest before the earlier of (i) expiry of a three (3) days period after delivery; and (ii) Buyer (or any other third party under Buyer's control) having driven at least one hundred kilometres (100 km) after delivery of the Vehicle. </p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">10.3 Any complaint must be thoroughly substantiated with all evidence necessary for CarSloter Europe or any third party to be able to determine the non-conformity of the Vehicle. For any external damage, Buyer shall provide clear pictures, together with an estimate of the value of the damage. For technical problems, Buyer shall notify the defect in accordance with clause 10.2 and as soon as possible thereafter (and in no case more than one (1) week after submission of the complaint) submit to CarSloter Europe a document from an official workshop or dealer which describes the technical damage and lists the ID numbers of the required spare parts.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">10.4 Pursuant to clause 9.2, to the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, no complaints can be made for Vehicles designated as "wrecked cars", “technical damaged cars”, “body damaged cars” and “accident cars” during the Auction.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">10.5 Please consult our claim policy document in your My account account for more detailed information.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;"> <a name="11">&nbsp;</a> </p>
                <h3 style="text-align: justify;">11.    Liability</h3>
                <br>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">11.1 To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, and subject to clause 11.3, CarSloter Europe shall not be liable for any direct or indirect or consequential damage of any kind, including without limitation disruption of business, third party claims and loss of profits, anticipated savings, or goodwill.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">11.2 To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, subject to clause 11.3, and to the extent clause 11.1, and/or any other limitations and exclusions of liability set out in these Terms and Conditions do not apply, CarSloter Europe's total aggregate liability</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">11.2.1 for any Losses of any nature incurred or suffered by Buyer arising out of or in connection with a CarSloter Europe Sale, shall not exceed the Offered Price for such CarSloter Europe Sale; and</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">11.2.2 for any other Losses incurred or suffered by Buyer shall, in each calendar year, in the exceptionnal event CarSloter Europe responsibility is undiscutably proven, be limited to the higher of (i) the Auction Fees and Country Fees paid by Buyer in such calendar year; and (ii) one thousand euros (EUR 1,000.00).</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">11.3 Neither Party shall exclude or limit its liability for (i) its own fraud or wilful intent; and /or (ii) any liability which cannot be excluded or limited under applicable law (in which case the relevant Party does not exclude or limit its liability only to the extent such exclusion or limitation is not permitted by applicable law).</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;"> <a name="12">&nbsp;</a> </p>
                <h3 style="text-align: justify;">12.    Blocking and Cancellations</h3>
                <br>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">12.1 Buyer does not have the right to cancel a CarSloter Europe Sale or any other order of an additional service for its convenience.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">12.2 If Buyer fails to comply with these Terms and Conditions, Buyer acknowledges and agrees that, without prejudice to CarSloter Europe's other rights and remedies under these Terms and Conditions, at law or otherwise CarSloter Europe reserves the right to temporarily or definitively block Buyer and its Users from accessing and using the Platform in any way. In such case,</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">12.2.1 CarSloter Europe will undertake reasonable efforts to inform Buyer of such blocking; and</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">12.2.2 CarSloter Europe may, in its sole discretion, decide to unblock Buyer and its Users subject to completion of a verification and validation process. This could be subject to payment of a reinstatement fee by Buyer.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">12.3 If, notwithstanding clause 12.1, Buyer wishes to cancel a CarSloter Europe Sale, Buyer may request such cancellation in writing or via e-mail. Buyer acknowledges and agrees that CarSloter Europe may, in its sole discretion, decide to refuse or allow such cancellation. If CarSloter Europe agrees to allow Buyer to cancel the CarSloter Europe Sale, Buyer shall pay to CarSloter Europe (i) all Auction Fees and Country Fees increased with applicable Taxes relating to such CarSloter Europe Sale; and (ii) ten per cent (10%) of the Offered Price relating to such CarSloter Europe Sale.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">12.4 Buyer does not have the right to cancel an additional service. If Buyer decides to cancel a CarSloter Europe order he will not be entitled to any kind of refund.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;"> <a name="13">&nbsp;</a> </p>
                <h3 style="text-align: justify;">13.    Invoicing and payment</h3>
                <br>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">13.1 This clause 13 shall apply to all fees and charges due by Buyer pursuant to a CarSloter Europe Sale or otherwise under these Terms and Conditions and any invoicing and payment thereof.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">13.2 Unless expressly stated otherwise, any fees, charges and amounts mentioned on the Platform and in these Terms and Conditions shall be in euros and exclusive of any applicable Taxes.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">13.3 Buyer acknowledges and agrees that any invoicing shall occur via E-Invoices and that Buyer shall not receive paper invoices. Buyer acknowledges and agrees that it is responsible for the fulfilment of all applicable legal requirements with respect to receipt and storage of E-Invoices.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">As an exception to the foregoing, Buyer can in the CarSloter Europe Sale Confirmation related to its first CarSloter Europe Sale, opt to choose for paper invoices in which case all invoices issued by CarSloter Europe to Buyer as from that moment shall be paper invoices.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">Buyer expressly acknowledges and accepts that CarSloter Europe shall charge an administrative fee of twenty five euros (EUR 25.00) for each paper invoice requested by Buyer, and such amount shall be added to each invoice.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">In case Buyer wishes to change its invoicing preferences after its first CarSloter Europe Sale, Buyer shall contact CarSloter Europe in accordance with clause 16.3 .</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">13.4 Without prejudice to CarSloter Europe's rights and remedies under these Terms and Conditions, at law or otherwise, if payment has not been credited to the bank account of CarSloter Europe</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">13.4.1 within the applicable payment term, CarSloter Europe is entitled to charge Buyer interest on overdue amounts, without prior notice, at a rate equal to the interest rate applicable under the Belgian Law of 2 August 2002 regarding late payment in commercial transactions; and</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">13.4.2 within two (2) weeks of confirmation of the CarSloter Europe Sale by CarSloter Europe, the CarSloter Europe Sale shall be deemed wrongfully cancelled by Buyer in accordance with clause 12.4.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">13.4.3 In case there are unpaid amounts emitted to the buyer, CarSloter Europe will have the right to block any other amount or vehicle in his possession, without advance notice, to compensate the unpaid amount. The blocked amount or vehicle shall not be limited to the same transactions but will be extended to all the open transactions between CarSloter Europe and the Buyer. </p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;"> <a name="14">&nbsp;</a> </p>
                <h3 style="text-align: justify;">14.    Privacy policy</h3>
                <br>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">14.1&nbsp;The policy includes important information about how CarSloter Europe collects and treats your data. <a data-cke-saved-href="https://www.CarSloter.eu/en/cms/privacy-policy?utm_source=newsflash&amp;utm_medium=e-mail&amp;utm_campaign=Newsflash20180518" href="https://www.CarSloter.eu/en/cms/privacy-policy" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline; color: #008c95;">Feel free to review our privacy policy here</span></a>.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;"> <a name="15">&nbsp;</a> </p>
                <h3 style="text-align: justify;">15.    Variations</h3>
                <br>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">15.1 CarSloter Europe may, at any time, amend, modify, add or delete any provision of these Terms and Conditions.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">15.2 CarSloter Europe will issue any such amended or new terms and conditions subject to a notice period of at least seven (7) calendar days. Buyer expressly acknowledges and agrees that such varied or new terms and conditions can be notified by CarSloter Europe to Buyer via electronic means, including via e-mail and/or notice on the Platform.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;">15.3 The amended or new terms and conditions shall apply and be deemed accepted by Buyer as from the date set out by CarSloter Europe, unless Buyer notifies CarSloter Europe in writing within the given notice period of its refusal to accept such varied or new terms and conditions. In such case, CarSloter Europe reserves the right to terminate these Terms and Conditions immediately without any compensation being due by CarSloter Europe in such respect, and to block Buyer and its Users' access and use of the Platform.</p>
                <p style="text-align: justify;"> <a name="16">&nbsp;</a> </p>
                <h3 style="text-align: justify;">16.    Miscellaneous</h3>
                <br>
